{
  "version": 2,
  "mode": "local",
  "auth": { "stepUp": ["email-code", "weekly-passphrase"] },
  "primary": "you",
  "users": [
    { "name": "you", "role": "admin", "path": "", "powers": ["knowledge"], "createdAt": "1970-01-01" }
  ],
  "_notes": "OPTIONAL multi-tenancy + access policy (v3.3). Absent ⇒ single-tenant at the repo root. `mode` is the use-case knob every frontend honors: 'local' (one user, no auth/isolation — a local notes app), 'open' (multi-user, partitions isolated at the OS layer, but switching is free — no auth), 'secure' (RBAC + step-up auth when an admin enters someone else's bound space). `auth.stepUp` = the secure-mode factors. A 'user' is an isolated knowledge partition; `role` admin|member, `powers` what they may do, `path` \"\"=repo root (primary) else users/<name>. This file is COMMITTED (no PII/secrets): identity handles (phone/email) live gitignored in identities.local.json; secrets in the OS keychain. memex DECLARES; the connected app ENFORCES. Set with `users.ts mode|add|remove`, slash commands, or a frontend."
}
